# kinematic-chain-hierarchy.md.disabled - README

This file was temporarily disabled on [2024-11-07] due to a duplicate requirement code issue.

## Issue:
Both `kinematic-chain-hierarchy.md` and `root-prim-xformable.md` are assigned the requirement code HI.007, 
which causes the documentation build to fail with a duplicate code error.

## Action Taken:
Renamed `kinematic-chain-hierarchy.md` to `kinematic-chain-hierarchy.md.disabled` to prevent 
the documentation build system from processing it.

## Resolution Needed:
The requirement codes need to be reviewed and one of these requirements should be assigned a different code.
This appears to be a pre-existing issue in the repository that needs to be resolved by the maintainers.

## To Re-enable:
Once the duplicate code issue is resolved, rename the file back to `kinematic-chain-hierarchy.md` 